From 8a78cb3f60d2e135bc9cc750e4175a4a8f25fcb6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bert Goemans <bert.goemans@softathome.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 10:10:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ubus: add ubus support for bridge and port configuration

Add OpenWrt ubus integration to enable dynamic bridge and port
configuration through the ubus IPC system. This allows netifd and
other OpenWrt components to control STP/RSTP/MSTP parameters at runtime.

Main ubus methods exposed:
- add_bridge: creates and configures a bridge with STP parameters
  Parameters: name, proto (stp/rstp/mstp), forward_delay, max_age,
              ageing_time, bridge_priority

- delete_bridge: removes a bridge from STP/RSTP/MSTP control
  Parameters: name

- set_port_config: configures per-port STP parameters
  Parameters: bridge, port, admin_edge_port, auto_edge_port,
              admin_p2p_port (Yes/No/Auto), path_cost, priority
